metadata.name: sin(city) #40
metadata.description:
cityscapes created from sine waves, noise, some patterns and light.

First click-> drawing process(visual + audio)

click->loop/noLoop

pres L -> turn on/off the lights.

Features:

  "num_layers": Number total of layers
  "max_height": Max Height
  "max_depth": Max depth
  "terrains": Sequence of 3 types of terrain of the cityscape(C->City, M->montain, W->water)
  "mist": % of mist.
  "clouds": number of clouds
  "sun_moon": has sun(moon) (boolean)
  "lights": type of lihgts
  "B_W": is black and white (boolean)
  "city_stroke": city buildings stroke(boolean)

-powered by 5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: Plottable Art Deco #40
metadata.description:
Initially made for #genuary 2023, JAN. 20 Art Deco prompt, a fxhash generator was generalized. It can yield various properties including x and y mirroring,

Meant to be plotted with a gold gel pen on a A4 dark blue paper.

"Introducing 'Plottable Art Deco', created for #genuary2023's Art Deco prompt. This fxhash generator is capable of producing unique properties such as x and y mirroring and other rare patterns, making every outcome truly one-of-a-kind. Designed to be plotted on A4 dark blue paper with a gold gel pen, this digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece.

Owning this NFT grants the right to plot or request a physical plot from the artist on https://greweb.me/plots/nft

The source code for this piece is available on GitHub at https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-artdeco, and is licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0.

metadata.name: COMPUTERS #21
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from pixel array computations and classic noise algorithms.

COMPUTERS is a meditation on the aesthetics of computing in all of its forms. It recalls the types of computation required to build temples, write complex texts, weave detailed textiles, and program computer games. Pixels have always existed in some form or another, before and after the screen. Every iteration of COMPUTERS suggests that computation is both contemporary and ancient.

Press 'p' or click to pause the animation.
Press 's' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: life is a (beautiful) mess #93
metadata.description:
when carefully applied, chaos brings things to life.

'life is a (beautiful) mess' was created as i led a certain amount of chaos take control of an animated textile algorithm i'm developing. 
as soon as it happened i realized that it was a great representation of our lives. 
each line represents one of us and the patterns that appear repeatedly are the situations we live which make us move, feel and be in a certain way. 
the image created is the sum of our paths in this life, as they only make sense when we look at them as one.

---

i hope you find it pleasant to watch this animation, how it develops and grows during aprox 1'30"
there are pieces drawn with the 4 typical school pen colors: black, green, blue and red. also a multicolor and a rare dark mode features.


press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the animation
doubleclick the mouse to resume the animation

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.name: Gardens of delusion #101
metadata.description:
We live in a perpetual state of assertive belief, and the outside world never faults us, because we escape contradiction through a process of delusion. How reassuring it is to wander in the alleys of subjectivity and take a seat to look at these gardens we create.

metadata.name: Stuck Inside #46
metadata.description:
As Spring transitions to Summer, flowers are in full bloom. With no outside view from my desk, I find myself daydreaming of walks around the yard, watering flowers, and watching the insects.

This is a simple and abstract kinetic piece that represents the daydreams I have while working, as I look forward to my next break, when I can walk outside for a few minutes.

100% of secondary sale royalties will go to the Processing Foundation.

The piece is responsive and will adapt to your browser window size. Press SPACE to export a high-resolution PNG image of the current frame at the current aspect ratio. 

If you are using Safari, the animation will be rate limited until you click or tap once on the piece.

metadata.name: Omega Point #38
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: Loom #102
metadata.description:
Loom is an exploration on texture, points, lines and noise on color in a gridsystem. 

You can self-curate your token, by clicking the canvas colors change in the cells, with the g key you can toggle between local change (cell) or global change (all cells), with the c key you can remove a color, with the v key you can reset colors, with the x key you can download a higher resolution version.


Press 's' to save a png image
Press 'j' to save a jpg image
Press 'x' to save a higher resolution png
Press 'c' to remove a color
Press 'v' to reset colors
